items.name: Re:Zero World v0.5 | Echidna, Rem, Ram, Elsa, Frederica, Felix, Subaru, Priscilla, Otto, Emilia, Beatrice, Petra
items.description:
Okay Novowels, i give up, here are characters.

Another experiment model based on re:zero characters. For now only 12 characters are more or less reliably usable. Others didn't have enough solo art, or a didn't have time to gather their character + character folders yet. That applies for most of side characters.

I had no time to gather more 2 characters for now, and no folders with 3 and more characters yet, so you'll have a hard time infering more than 2 characters at a time without using additional tools. 2 character inference is supported, but only for limited character set, like Ram + Rem. Other than that, you'll have hard time trying to get together other characters, other than main cast.

While quality is quite mid by my standards(for characters), i don't have hardware capability to make better at the current moment in time, as multi-character models are harder to train. If you want to help with that - https://ko-fi.com/anzhc xD

So far characters that are supported: Echidna, Rem, Ram, Elsa, Frederica, Felix, Subaru, Priscilla, Otto, Emilia, Beatrice, Petra

Beatrice and Petra are trained only on their SFW fan-art.

I plan to expand it as much as i can, though, my patience and sleeping time is already at limits, as training took over 10 hours at current dataset already.

Im just testing how things go on Locon model with wider arrangement of characters when you don't balance them out. In this particular dataset i tried to keep character datasets at 100 images, but some, like Echidna and Rem are based on 170 and 125 respectively. Less popular characters, like Frederica and Otto, don't have much images, so their datasets are scarse. That is also a reason why current version is limited only to 12 characters, while total folder amount of unique characters is ~16-18, some of them, like Patrasche, almost don't have art, and solo image was only one in that particular case on Danbooru. This will be offset with combo folders of dataset in future, like curently i have Ram + Rem, or Rem + Emilia and so on, but that requires time, and especially training time.

Current version was trained with 10 classification images per dataset one to not train style(to respect artists' work in that regard) and train character features better, which amounted to over 11k images that i had to generate for roughly 2 hours straight, to just start training, which totalled at over 110k steps. I will drop usage of class for future trainings, unless by miracle someone gifts me a server dedicated to train stuff, so i can save time and sanity. I will not be concerned with copying anyones' style at dataset counts of over 2k images, but that is also going to be over 100k steps of training, which will mean ~8-12 hours of training.

I do strip artists names, so it is not possible to infer their style without model that already has them embedded.

items.name: Fresh Draw (anime-manga eddiemauro-mix)
items.description:
Before to use

  • You have to know how works Stable Diffusion. I recommend using Automatic1111 like an interface to launch the model.

  • This is a model trained on SD 1.5 model, so you have to consider that it is not perfect. I had to make so much testing before to arrive to a stable generation. I will enhance the model when a better base model arrives (like SD XL new one).

  • This is a Checkpoint dataset.

  • I recommend you to follow me on my instagram account, where I will explain about AI image generation: https://www.instagram.com/eddiemauro.design/

Intro

FRESH DRAW (anime and manga eddiemauro-mix): CHECKPOINT: Hi, I‚Äôm a product and car designer, and I‚Äôm so excited to test with AI, I think is a good tool for designing. It was created by combining some models here from civitai, with a style of anime, manga and drawing. It is a good model for art-drawing (2D) representation. Furthermore, it has vivid color mostly, but you can control it with prompt. It is good to adapt to different Lora drawing styles. Likewise, it has a little influence from my "Fresh Mix Series" models.

If you want to support my work and help me to upload more models (with better quality), you can do it by entering here and donating, I would greatly appreciate it: https://ko-fi.com/eddiemauro

Installation

  • I use Automatic1111, the best UI for Stable Diffusion image generation, so I recommend you to install locally or use it online with some Colab or other hosting. You can find online instructions or videos to do that. If you are going to install locally, you can watch this tutorial online and I recommend you to have at least a 6-8 Gb of VRAM Graphic Card (nvidia) to have a stable interface and launch with ‚ÄúMicrosoft Edge‚Äù because you will have problems on ‚ÄúGoogle Chrome‚Äù. Try also to install ‚Äúmedvram‚Äù or ‚Äúlowvram‚Äù options besides ‚Äúxformers‚Äù (search online how to).

  • You have to install the Checkpoint model to use.

  • Please for image creation you have to follow all my recommendations, if you don't, it is impossible to generate a good image quality. Also, you have to consider that from today AI image generation is not so consistent and perfect, you have to invest time to get it and make plenty of tests.

Recommendations for image generation

  • Activation token/caption: Put in the first part of the prompt: "Illustration of", "Drawing of" or "Sketching of", to put more art style into the image, but is not mandatory.

  • NSFW: This model is not recommended for kids, and also whole CIVITAI. Try to put in Negative prompt: "((NSFW)), Cleavage, Pubic Hair, Nudity, Naked, Au naturel, Watermark, Text, censored". If you don't want to see something that you "don't want" to see, just don't use this model, and even that, don't visit civitai. After so many tests, I consider that this model has a normal level of NSFW content, taking in account that this is a mix.

  • Another recommended prompting: Inside prompt you can use those words that will enhance the image generation: in the positive space, ‚Äú8k, ((masterpiece)), artstation, highly detailed, sharp focus‚Äù; in the negative space: ‚Äú(worst quality:2), (low quality:2), (normal quality:2), lowres, cropped, text, jpeg artifacts, signature, watermark, username, blurry, realistic, render, out of frame‚Äù. You can also watch the image metadata of example images here and simulate the prompt.

  • Textual inversion/embedding or Lora tool recommended: I consider that ‚ÄúEasyNegative‚Äù is one best of textual inversion for negative prompt space, you should use it. Download here and install it, putting the file inside ‚Äúembeddings‚Äù. You can use it also ‚ÄúDetail Tweaker‚Äù to put more details of the image, for that, you have to download from here, install like a Lora and use it inside positive prompt with a value of ‚Äú1‚Äù. Use it when you realize the checkpoint used has so many details, but not when you see that minimalism is on it.

  • VAE: For sketch style is mandatory to use "kl-f8-anime2". Download and install if you don't have it.

  • Clip Skip: Use 2.

  • Steps and CFG: It is recommended to use Steps from ‚Äú20-40‚Äù and CFG scale from ‚Äú7-9‚Äù, the ideal is: steps 30, CFG 8. For next models, those values could change.

  • Sampler: I use mostly ‚ÄúEulerA‚Äù or ‚ÄúDPM++SDE Karras‚Äù. Euler tends to be simpler and more creative. Make experimentation with other samplers if you like.

  • Batch: In txt2img try to put a value of 4 to generate more than 1 image and watch the generations. If you have a good graphic card, you can use ‚ÄúBatch size‚Äù, this will create at same time 4 images, increasing generation time; but if your computer cannot handle this, change to ‚ÄúBatch count‚Äù that will create 4 images in a row (not a same time), but generation time will be more.

  • Image aspect: Try to use these dimensions: 512x512, 768x512, 512x768. Don't generate bigger images because the style could be lost, if you want to create a bigger image, use hires.fix in txt2img mode, img2img increase method or Ultimate SD Upscale script extension + ControlNet, or just upscaling with GAN models.

  • Create bigger images: There are 4 different methods to create large images in Stable Diffusion, you can check online how to. For first method ‚Äútxt2img hires.fix‚Äù, I recommend you to use upscale model called ‚Äú4x-AnimeSharp‚Äù, downloading here just ‚Äú.pth‚Äù file, and then installing it, putting inside ‚ÄúESRGAN‚Äù file. In hires.fix option put any ‚Äúupscale by‚Äù value, and then with a ‚Äúdenoise strength‚Äù of ‚Äú0.5-0.7‚Äù. For the second method, you have to select first the image generated in txt2img and then putting in img2img mode, increasing dimension at least ‚Äú1,5 times‚Äù with a ‚Äúdenoise strength‚Äù from ‚Äú0.3-0.5‚Äù. For the third method, you can use the same configuration of img2img, but activating ‚Äútile‚Äù mode of ‚ÄúControlNet‚Äù extension and also the script of ‚ÄúUltimate SD Upscale‚Äù, but for that, I recommend you to watch a tutorial here. For the last method, you have to pass the generated image in txt2img to ‚Äúextras‚Äù and then select a GAN model and scale it, you can also use the ‚Äú4x-UltraSharp‚Äù model.

  • Get more control of your creation: Use ‚ÄúControlNet‚Äù extension to generate a more controlled shape of what you want, and even you can test it with sketches. Use ‚ÄúScribble‚Äù or ‚ÄúLineart‚Äù modes. For that, I recommend you to install this extension and then learn to how to use. There are plenty of online videos about it.

  • Copy prompt for image metadata: You can download my example images here and put it inside ‚ÄúPNG info‚Äù tab from Automatic1111.

Example Prompting:

Positive prompt:¬†

[description here, example: "Illustration of a man holding a sword ...] then you can add whatever you want .... 8k, ((masterpiece)), artstation, highly detailed, sharp focus

Negative prompt:¬†

EasyNegative, (worst quality:2), (low quality:2), (normal quality:2), out of frame, blurry

Steps: from 20-40 (Use DPM++SDE Karras or EulerA)

CFG scale: 7-9 (8 Ideal).

What comes for the future

I‚Äôm already trying to enhance the model. This was trained with 512 image aspect, so I will try with 768 (bigger one), and also other configurations (like changing captions, steps, epochs, etc.). If you like a better model of this version, try to keep supporting me on ko-fi, if there are more people supporting me, I can invest more time to train and enhance models, but if this doesn't happen I cannot.¬†

I launched my first private model for my Ko-fi membership lv.1, called "eddiemauro scene" minimalistic scenery creation for rendering. If you want to access to private models, you can support me and subscribe to this membership. I will also start to upload here more models centered on product and car design.
